Hi all,
I design and run all the lights for my high school and lately we've
been having problems with the sound and lights interfering with one
another. We have a sound system that allows us to switch between
theatre (includes overhead mics) and main (no overhead mics). The
problem I'm having is that if I use the main mode the lights work fine
and theres no interference, but if i have it on theatre mode a loud
buzz comes out of the speakers when i bring the lights up and down but
not when they are at 100 or 0 power. I talked to someone in the school
about getting it looked at but they said a factor in determining how/if
it would get fixed was money. Any suggestions about possible causes??
We are presenting the Music Man at the end of March and it will be
really hard to deal with that because there aregoing to be quite a few
lighting changes.
