<POSTER> "gizmo" &lt;ccgizmo...@aol.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-01-23T20:49:00 </POSTDATE>
if its only when its dimmed, not full,  it sounds like the electricial
noise the dimmers generate. By the nature of how they dim, they
generate quite a bit of noise.  im not exactly sure how to fix it, but
maybe hooking the two systems to different circuits if they arent
already?  also, if the microphone cables are near the power wires, they
may be picking up the noise. try moving the wires (mics, light power
cables, or both) to a different location farther away from eachother.
also, check all the groundings/ shieldings on all the cables- if your
using a snake its possible that the shielding is broken somewhere. im
not sure if / where they have it, but some sort of extra shielding for
the mic cables probably cant hurt.
hope this helps

